CRC Credit Bureau Limited has appointed Mrs. Jelilat Kareem as its Group Chief Operating Officer (GCOO) of the company. This appointment took effect from January 1, 2022. Mrs. Kareem will oversee the Finance, Enterprise Wide Services, Operations, and Technology of the Group, driving global best practices.   Fidelity Bank’s GAIM 5 promo winners get N10m     Microwork pilot promotes financial inclusion     Akintayo joins Forbes   Prior to this appointment, she was the Head of Finance and Corporate Services of the organisation. Mrs Kareem has over 24 years‘ experience in start-up management, accounting and finance, treasury management, credit and risk management, strategy, human resources management, governance and corporate services, including systems/policy formulation and analysis. The Group Managing Director/CEO of CRC Credit Bureau Limited, Dr. ‘Tunde Popoola, said: “From the business perspective, Jelilat brings to her new role, both a broad and practical experience with a variety of public and private companies.  She has in-depth expertise in financial regulations and processes. She is highly respected in her field, and we are excited to continue working with her in this capacity to meet our corporate strategic goals.”